# Tonk UI Styling

## CSS Modules
- Use CSS modules for component-specific styling
- Name CSS files with `.module.css` extension to match component files
- Import styles with meaningful names like `styles` or descriptive names

## Lists and Navigation
- For clickable lists, use `cursor: pointer` on items
- Add hover effects (like text-decoration: underline) for interactive elements
- Use standard list-style-type with appropriate padding for bullet points
- Include adequate spacing between list items with padding

## Layout
- Use viewport units (vh, vw) for responsive container sizing
- Apply appropriate padding for content areas
- Use calc() for dynamic sizing when needed 